  "prompt": "What marks and rank is required to get Aerospace Engineering in IIT Bombay in JEE Advanced 2017?",
  "response": "The marks and rank required to secure a seat in Aerospace Engineering at IIT Bombay through JEE Advanced can vary each year due to changes in the number of applicants, difficulty level of the exam, and seat availability. However, historically, one needs to secure a high rank to gain admission to such prestigious programs.\n\nTo give a rough idea, in JEE Advanced 2017:\n- A rank within approximately the top 700-800 would be required for the General category to get Aerospace Engineering at IIT Bombay.\n- For OBC category, typically within the top 500-600 rank.\n- For SC/ST categories, the rank can be lower due to reserved seats.\n\nThe exact cutoff ranks can differ, so it's best to check the official opening and closing ranks released by IIT Bombay after each counselling session for precise information.",
